The paper deals with information theory and combinatorics, specifically in the context of binary strings and subsequences. The use of clustering techniques and the focus on entropy minimization suggest a strong connection to information theory (cs.IT). The use of run-length encoding and the enumeration of supersequences and singletons suggest a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and combinatorics (cs.DM). The use of algorithms and closed form expressions suggest a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC) and machine learning (cs.LG).
